It seems cleaner to do this, then you aren't breaking down the string into an array and then building it up again, you are just splitting the string at two points if and only if it has a dash.

```
var dashpos = trackInfo.title.indexOf('-');
// assign both and they can work it out if no dashes
var title = trackInfo.title;
var artist = trackInfo.title;
// if there is a dash, set them in the assumed format [title] - [artist]
if(dashpos != -1){
  // part of string before dash
  title = trackInfo.title.substr(0, dashpos);
  // part of string after dash
  artist = trackInfo.title.substr(dashpos + 1);
}
```

Also a side note, maybe we should set the artist and the album to be the rest of the string? in case it contains both the user can strip them down?

