The bug is in `filter_view::__iterator::operator--`:
```diff
 constexpr __iterator& operator--() requires BidirectionalRange<V>
 {
     do
         --current_;
-    while(__stl2::invoke(parent_->pred_.get(), *current_));
+    while(!__stl2::invoke(parent_->pred_.get(), *current_));
     return *this;
 }
```
It's searching for the previous element that *doesn't* satisfy the predicate rather than the previous element that *does*. I fixed this months ago in the Ranges proposal, and assumed it was a typo that had been introduced during all the editing work. It never occurred to me that the bug might have been copied directly from the implementation.

